<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1892-09-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1892-09-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="500" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d500">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Scruggs</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Foster</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Caracas</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1892-09-24"><hi rend="italic">September 24, 1892</hi></date>.
                            (Received September 24.)</dateline></opener>
                    <p>Mr. Scruggs reports that the situation remains unchanged, nothing new having
                        occurred, and transmits a request of the Government of Venezuela that the
                        steamer <hi rend="italic">South Portland</hi>, laden with munitions of war
                        in New York, be prevented from entering Puerto Cabello by the naval forces
                        of the United States.</p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>